question:
An electron is in the spin state (3i, 4). Find the expectation value of its spin along y-direction, S_y.
Note: \sigma_y (in latex format) is: 
\begin{pmatrix}
0 & -i \\
i & 0
\end{pmatrix}

answers.deepseek:
\boxed{
V(\vec{r}, t) = \frac{1}{4 \pi \epsilon_0} \left(\frac{q}{\kappa d}\right)_{\text{ret}} = \frac{1}{4 \pi \epsilon_0} \left(\frac{q}{d - \frac{\vec{v} \cdot \vec{d}}{c}}\right)_{\text{ret}}.
}
\boxed{
\vec{A}(\vec{r}, t) = \frac{\mu_0}{4 \pi} \left(\frac{q \vec{v}}{\kappa d}\right)_{\text{ret}} = \frac{\mu_0}{4 \pi} \left(\frac{q \vec{v}}{d - \frac{\vec{v} \cdot \vec{d}}{c}}\right)_{\text{ret}}.
}
